COMMAND validate-adapter
SYNOPSIS: fdd-cli validate adapter <path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate FDD adapter configuration files for correctness and completeness
WORKFLOW: @FDD.workflows.adapter-config

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <directory>  required  Path to adapter directory (e.g., spec/FDD-Adapter)

OPTIONS:
  --json  <boolean>  Output results in JSON format for machine consumption
  --verbose, -v  <boolean>  Enable detailed output with file-by-file validation
  --quiet, -q  <boolean>  Minimal output (errors only)

OUTPUT:
  type: gts.ainetx.fdd-cli.validation.validation_result.v1
  format: Human-readable report or JSON (with --json flag)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Adapter is valid and complete
  1  Adapter validation failed (missing or incorrect files)
  2  Adapter is incomplete (missing specifications)

EXAMPLE:
  $ fdd-cli validate adapter spec/FDD-Adapter
  $ fdd-cli validate adapter spec/FDD-Adapter --json
  $ fdd-cli validate adapter spec/FDD-Adapter --verbose

RELATED:
  - @Workflow.adapter-config
  - @CLI.init

