COMMAND validate-architecture
SYNOPSIS: fdd-cli validate architecture <path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate Overall Design document against FDD requirements (requires ≥90/100 score)
WORKFLOW: @FDD.workflows.02-validate-architecture

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <path>  required  Path to architecture directory or DESIGN.md file

OPTIONS:
  --json  <boolean>  Output results in JSON format for machine consumption
  --verbose, -v  <boolean>  Enable detailed validation output with line-by-line analysis
  --quiet, -q  <boolean>  Minimal output (score and blocking issues only)

OUTPUT:
  type: gts.ainetx.fdd-cli.validation.validation_result.v1
  format: Detailed validation report with score, issues, and recommendations

EXIT CODES:
  0  Overall Design is valid (score ≥90/100)
  1  Overall Design validation failed (score <90/100 or critical issues)
  2  File not found or invalid format

EXAMPLE:
  $ fdd-cli validate architecture architecture/
  $ fdd-cli validate architecture architecture/DESIGN.md --json
  $ fdd-cli validate architecture . --verbose

RELATED:
  - @Workflow.02-validate-architecture
  - @Workflow.03-init-features
  - @CLI.validate-feature

