COMMAND validate-feature
SYNOPSIS: fdd-cli validate feature <path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate Feature Design document for completeness and correctness (requires 100/100 score + 100% completeness)
WORKFLOW: @FDD.workflows.06-validate-feature

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <path>  required  Path to feature directory or feature DESIGN.md file

OPTIONS:
  --json  <boolean>  Output results in JSON format for machine consumption
  --verbose, -v  <boolean>  Enable detailed validation with section-by-section analysis
  --quiet, -q  <boolean>  Minimal output (score and blocking issues only)
  --strict  <boolean>  Enable strict validation mode (all warnings become errors)

OUTPUT:
  type: gts.ainetx.fdd-cli.validation.validation_result.v1
  format: Comprehensive validation report with score, completeness percentage, and issues

EXIT CODES:
  0  Feature Design is valid (100/100 score + 100% completeness)
  1  Feature Design validation failed (score <100 or completeness <100%)
  2  File not found or invalid format

EXAMPLE:
  $ fdd-cli validate feature architecture/features/feature-validation/
  $ fdd-cli validate feature architecture/features/feature-validation/DESIGN.md --json
  $ fdd-cli validate feature architecture/features/feature-validation/ --strict

RELATED:
  - @Workflow.06-validate-feature
  - @Workflow.09-openspec-init
  - @CLI.validate-architecture

