COMMAND validate-manifest
SYNOPSIS: fdd-cli validate manifest <path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate FEATURES.md manifest for structure, dependencies, and consistency
WORKFLOW: @FDD.workflows.04-validate-features

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <path>  required  Path to FEATURES.md file

OPTIONS:
  --json  <boolean>  Output results in JSON format for machine consumption
  --verbose, -v  <boolean>  Enable detailed validation with dependency graph analysis
  --quiet, -q  <boolean>  Minimal output (errors only)
  --check-cycles  <boolean>  [default: true]  Check for circular dependencies

OUTPUT:
  type: gts.ainetx.fdd-cli.validation.validation_result.v1
  format: Manifest validation report with dependency analysis

EXIT CODES:
  0  Manifest is valid and consistent
  1  Manifest validation failed (structural or dependency issues)
  2  File not found or invalid format
  3  Circular dependency detected

EXAMPLE:
  $ fdd-cli validate manifest architecture/features/FEATURES.md
  $ fdd-cli validate manifest architecture/features/FEATURES.md --json
  $ fdd-cli validate manifest architecture/features/FEATURES.md --verbose

RELATED:
  - @Workflow.04-validate-features
  - @Workflow.03-init-features
  - @CLI.validate-feature

