COMMAND init
SYNOPSIS: fdd-cli init [path] [options]
DESCRIPTION: Initialize FDD project structure with directories and template files
WORKFLOW: @FDD.workflows.01-init-project

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <directory>  optional  Target directory for project initialization (defaults to current directory)

OPTIONS:
  --json  <boolean>  Output results in JSON format for machine consumption
  --verbose, -v  <boolean>  Enable detailed output showing each created file and directory
  --quiet, -q  <boolean>  Minimal output (errors only)
  --force  <boolean>  Overwrite existing files (use with caution)

OUTPUT:
  type: gts.ainetx.fdd-cli.project.project_structure.v1
  format: List of created directories and files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Project structure initialized successfully
  1  Initialization failed (permissions or existing files conflict)
  2  Invalid target directory

EXAMPLE:
  $ fdd-cli init
  $ fdd-cli init ./my-project
  $ fdd-cli init --verbose
  $ fdd-cli init --force

RELATED:
  - @Workflow.01-init-project
  - @CLI.generate-structure
  - @CLI.validate-architecture

