COMMAND generate-structure
SYNOPSIS: fdd-cli generate structure <design-path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Generate folder structure from Overall Design or Feature Design document
WORKFLOW: None (utility command)

ARGUMENTS:
  design-path  <path>  required  Path to DESIGN.md file (Overall or Feature Design)

OPTIONS:
  --json  <boolean>  Output results in JSON format for machine consumption
  --verbose, -v  <boolean>  Enable detailed output showing generation process
  --quiet, -q  <boolean>  Minimal output (errors only)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be created without actually creating files

OUTPUT:
  type: gts.ainetx.fdd-cli.project.project_structure.v1
  format: List of created or would-be-created directories

EXIT CODES:
  0  Structure generated successfully
  1  Generation failed (permissions or I/O error)
  2  Design file not found or invalid format
  3  Required information missing in design document

EXAMPLE:
  $ fdd-cli generate structure architecture/DESIGN.md
  $ fdd-cli generate structure architecture/features/feature-auth/DESIGN.md --dry-run
  $ fdd-cli generate structure architecture/DESIGN.md --json

RELATED:
  - @CLI.init
  - @Workflow.05-init-feature

